  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghan Civilian Assistance Program (ACAP) III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Afghanistan):  The Afghanistan Civilian Assistance Project (ACAP III) activity will continue to aid in the recovery and reintegration of war victims, and contribute to the overall humanitarian efforts that support conditions for longer-term development in Afghanistan.  ACAP-III will provide socio-economic assistance to Afghan individuals and families who have suffered economic livelihood losses, injuries, and losses of life from kinetic activities, explosive remnants of war (ERWs), and landmines. ACAP III will increase the capacity of the Afghan government to identify and respond to the needs of victims of war as part of the wider plan to transition the program to Afghan leadership. ACAP III will also increase advocacy and public awareness on the needs of people with disabilities, disability rights, and the risks posed by landmines and ERWs to the general public, and in particular, to communities and schools located in places considered most vulnerable.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objectives for Afghanistan: Distribute immediate assistance packages, consisting of food items and household materials, to eligible civilian beneficiaries Provide physical rehabilitation services to eligible civilian beneficiaries as appropriate. Provide economic re-integration assistance to restore lost livelihoods, such as jobs and business skills. Provide psychosocial counseling services. Build the capacity of government institutions to support victim assistance initiatives in the long term</narrative>
  </description>
